ðŸŸ¦ Problem Paragraph
Implement a Student Database Management System using a Binary Search Tree (BST).
Each student record contains a roll number, name, and grades.
The BST is organized using the roll number as the key.
The system should support the following operations:
Add a student
Delete a student using roll number
Search for a student using roll number
Display all students in ascending order of roll numbers using in-order traversal
Exit the program
All grades must be displayed rounded to two decimal places.
ðŸŸ¦ Input Format
The first line contains an integer choice, representing the operation to perform.
Choice 1 (Add Student)
Next three lines contain:
Roll number (integer)
Name (string)
Grades (float)
Choice 2 (Delete Student)
Next line contains the roll number to delete.
Choice 3 (Search Student)
Next line contains the roll number to search.
Choice 4 (Display Database)
No additional input.
Choice 5 (Exit Program)
No additional input.
The program continues until choice 5 is entered.
ðŸŸ¦ Output Format
For Delete Student:
Student not found. if the roll number does not exist.
For Search Student:
If found:
Student found - Roll Number: <roll>, Name: <name>, Grades: <grades>
Else:
Student not found.
For Display Database:
Copy code

Student Database (inorder):
Roll Number: <roll>, Name: <name>, Grades: <grades>
For Exit Program:
Exiting program.
ðŸŸ¦ Code Constraints
ï¿½ roll number ï¿½
ï¿½ length(name) ï¿½
ï¿½ grades ï¿½
ï¿½ total students ï¿½
ðŸŸ¦ Sample Test Case (One Combined Flow)
Input
Copy code

1
101
John
85.5
1
102
Jane
92.0
1
105
